A heavy silence falls over the stewards office as he utters that number. 2,640 crowns. In the world of Battle Brothers, that is not just a paymentit is a death sentence for the unprepared. Garcia the Steward is essentially offering you a small fortune to walk into a blender.

The Analysis of the Void

Geists. These are not "training dummies" like the bandit rabble you just harvested. Geists are ethereal horrors that:

  • Cannot be hit easily (high defense).

  • Ignore armor with their screams.

  • Scream to break the Resolve of your entire line, turning brave men into fleeing cowards in a single turn.

The Risk: If your men break and flee, the Geists will simply float after them and slice them down. Jan F and your newer recruits are at extreme risk here; their Resolve is likely brittle. Arnulf, being undead, might be your most reliable anchor, as he knows no fear.

The Asset: The Steward specifically mentioned NeCola. As a Vatt'ghern, she is built for this. Her increased initiative and potential for high-damage bursts are your best bet to "delete" the Geists before they can let out a second scream.

Preparing for the "Drafty Shack"

With over 4,000 crowns currently in your purse and another 2,640 promised, you have the capital to prepare properly. Before you head south-east:

  1. Bolster Resolve: Do you have any trophies or gear that increases Bravery? If not, a trip to the Tavern for a round of drinks might temporarily boost morale before the march.

  2. The Sergeant: Do you have a brother with high Resolve to act as a Rallying point? If a Geist screams and the "Usurper's Bane" starts to run, you need someone to yell them back into formation.

  3. Weaponry: Geists have almost no HP but are hard to hit. Fast, accurate weapons (Spears/Swords) or reaching weapons (Pikes) are better than heavy axes here.

The Decision

The "Drafty Shack" lies to the south-east. The air already feels colder just thinking about it.

  • [Accept]: "The Abyss fears no ghosts. We march at dawn."

  • [Prepare First]: Spend some of your 4,000 crowns in the Fuhrtmark market on better helmets or Resolve-boosting items before leaving.

  • [Haggle/Inquire]: Ask the Steward if he has any more information on how many Geists were seen.
